  • Classes in streamcorpus used by streamcorpus 
    Class and Description
    Annotator
    An Annotator object describes a human (or possibly a set of humans) who generated the data stored in a Label or Rating object.
    Annotator._Fields
    The set of fields this struct contains, along with convenience methods for finding and manipulating them.
    ContentItem
    ContentItem contains raw data, an indication of its character encoding, and various transformed versions of the raw data.
    ContentItem._Fields
    The set of fields this struct contains, along with convenience methods for finding and manipulating them.
    EntityType
    Different tagging tools have different strings for labeling the various common entity types.
    Label
    Labels are human generated assertions about a portion of a document For example, a human author might label their own text by inserting hyperlinks to Wikipedia, or a NIST assessor might record which tokens in a text mention a target entity.
    Label._Fields
    The set of fields this struct contains, along with convenience methods for finding and manipulating them.
    Language
    Description of a natural language used in text
    Language._Fields
    The set of fields this struct contains, along with convenience methods for finding and manipulating them.
    Offset
    Offset specifies a range within a field of data in this ContentItem
    Offset._Fields
    The set of fields this struct contains, along with convenience methods for finding and manipulating them.
    OffsetType
    Offset and OffsetType are used by Annotation to identify the portion of a ContentItem that a human labeled with a tag.
    Rating
    Ratings are buman generated assertions about a entire document's utility for a particular topic or entity in a reference KB.
    Rating._Fields
    The set of fields this struct contains, along with convenience methods for finding and manipulating them.
    Sentence 
    Sentence._Fields
    The set of fields this struct contains, along with convenience methods for finding and manipulating them.

    StreamItem._Fields
    The set of fields this struct contains, along with convenience methods for finding and manipulating them.
    StreamTime
    StreamTime is a timestamp measured in seconds since the 1970 epoch.
    StreamTime._Fields
    The set of fields this struct contains, along with convenience methods for finding and manipulating them.
    Tagging 
    Tagging._Fields
    The set of fields this struct contains, along with convenience methods for finding and manipulating them.
    Target
    Targets are "informationt targets," such as entities or topics, usually from a knowledge base, such as Wikipedia.
    Target._Fields
    The set of fields this struct contains, along with convenience methods for finding and manipulating them.
    Token
    Textual tokens identified by an NLP pipeline and marked up with metadata from automatic taggers and possibly also Labels from humans.
    Token._Fields
    The set of fields this struct contains, along with convenience methods for finding and manipulating them.
    Versions
    Versions of this protocol are enumerated so that when we expand, everybody can see which version a particular data file used.
